pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants, shoes plus socks, and chemical-resistant gloves made of any waterproof material, such as nitrile, butyl, neoprene and/or barrier laminate.

Active_Ingredients.name: Fluoxastrobin
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Interferes with respiration in plant-pathogenic fungi and inhibits spore germination and mycelial growth

Safety_Information.general_Info: CAUTION: Prolonged or frequently repeated skin contact may cause allergic reactions in some individuals. Avoid contact with skin, eyes or clothing.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15 - 20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not give anything to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor or going for treatment.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15 - 20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
